<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ890728-0179 </DOCNO><DD> = 890728 </DD><AN> 890728-0179. </AN><HL> Letters to the Editor:@  One Language </HL><DD> 07/28/89 </DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J) </SO><TEXT>   Regarding your June 29 article &quot;Demand for Hispanic Ads Outstrips Specialists in Field.&quot; Would it be in order for you to editorialize on the need for one language -- and one language only? We all have seen and heard of the problems arising from dual languages -- in Canada (Quebec) and other locations. It would seem to be beneficial for our country to have one language only. Just what is it with Spanish-speaking people that they demand we use &quot;their&quot; language?    Charles H. Badger    Chicago </TEXT></DOC>